## Summary

**Changed file:** `bb001_wordfreq/cli.py` — replaced `action="store_true"` (which ignored the value) with `type=int` on the `--min-length` argument, so `--min-length N` parses as an integer that flows into `count_words(min_length=N)`. Default stays `0`, preserving behavior when the flag is omitted.

**Verification:**
```
$ pytest -q
..                                                                       [100%]
2 passed in 0.07s
```

No other files changed; no tests added since the existing `test_min_length_filters_short_words` already covers the fixed behavior.
